ice to the person of an intention to suspend the WWVP</p><p style="text-align: center;">registration; and</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">b) has considered any reasons given by the person in accordance withthe notice; and</p><p style="text-align: center;">c)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">is satisfied that the grounds for suspension or cancellation under section 57 exist.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Suspension of WWVP registration</p><p style="text-align: center;">On 13 January 2021 you were provided with a written notice of proposed suspension (the</p><p style="text-align: center;">Notice}. The Notice informed you of the Commissioner's intention to suspend your WWVP</p><p style="text-align: center;">registration while new relevant information is considered as part of an additional risk</p><p style="text-align: center;">assessment. The Notice provided you with an opportunity to give reasons why your WWVP</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">registration should not be suspended. A copy of the Notice, including the new relevant</p><p style="text-align: center;">information is at Attachment A.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Chief Minister, Treasury and Economic Development</p><p style="text-align: center;">GPO Box 158 Canberra ACT 2601 | phone: 132281 | www.act.gov.au</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ï¿½On 15 January 2021, the Commissioner received your response to the Notice which included</p><p style="text-align: center;">the following:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â®</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">You are too late because | have already accomplished everything that God has required</p><p style="text-align: center;">of me. You evil demons are now exposed for what you are. | will not pass on the</p><p style="text-align: center;">information to prove this because in the Bible it tells me net to give my pearls to pigs</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">who will turn and attack me. | did what | needed with your evil card and now you will</p><p style="text-align: center;">burn. This is a moral complaint about your conduct. You will go down in histor</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">disgraceful actionsâ€.</p><p style="text-align: center;">| amsatisfied that you were provided with a written notice of proposecagg</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">considered the reasons given by you, as outlined above and cannot be satisfied that you have</p><p style="text-align: center;">orovided sufficient evidence to treat the identified risk. Further, consistent withthe Notice</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">provided to you and with sections 54 and 57(2} of the Act, lam satisfied on reasonable</p><p style="text-align: center;">grounds that new relevant information exists that must be riskassessed, and that itis</p><p style="text-align: center;">appropriate to suspend your registration while this is being completed. Accordingly, the</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Commissioner must suspend your WWVP registration while the additional risk assessment is</p><p style="text-align: center;">conducted, in accordance with section 59(1) of the Act.</p><p style="text-align: center;">As of 21 January 2021, you are prohibited from engaging ina regulated activity while the</p><p style="text-align: center;">additional risk assessment is conducted.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Return of registration card</p><p style="text-align: center;">You are required by law to return your registration card to Access Canberra byno later than</p><p style="text-align: c