</p><p style="text-align: center;">P Please consider the environment - do you really need to print this email?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â </p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I acknowledge and pay my respects to the traditional owners and custodians on whose land I walk, work & live.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">cid:image002.png@01D6238B.715C50B0</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â </p><p style="text-align: center;">12 April 2021</p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Wendell Nesmith</p><p style="text-align: center;">1/11 Howie Court</p><p style="text-align: center;">BELCONNEN ACT 2617</p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Mr Nesmith</p><p style="text-align: center;">Mental health, 21G350035X</p><p style="text-align: center;">I refer to your request for reconsideration of the decision to refuse you a grant of assistance</p><p style="text-align: center;">in this matter.</p><p style="text-align: center;">In reconsidering your application for a grant of legal assistance I am bound to follow the</p><p style="text-align: center;">Legal Aid Act 1977 and the Legal Assistance Guidelines (the Guidelines) made thereunder. I</p><p style="text-align: center;">have carefully considered your reconsideration request and the documents on your file</p><p style="text-align: center;">however I regret to advise I now confirm the decision to refuse you a grant of legal</p><p style="text-align: center;">assistance in this matter because it is not reasonable to spend scarce legal aid funds in</p><p style="text-align: center;">circumstances where prospects of success are outside our guidelines of more likely than not</p><p style="text-align: center;">to succeed.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Upon reconsideration it is also necessary, pursuant to section 39 of the Legal Aid Act 1977,</p><p style="text-align: center;">to have regard to funds available to the Commission and to the nature and extent of the</p><p style="text-align: center;">legal assistance that has been provided from those funds. Those funds are limited.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Although on reconsideration your application for legal assistance has been refused, I remind</p><p style="text-align: center;">you that Legal Aid ACT offers the following free services which may assist you, particularly in</p><p style="text-align: center;">regards to seeking advice and/or assistance in relation to the review of your current order</p><p style="text-align: center;">prior to its expiry:</p><p style="text-align: center;">1. A 30 minute appointment with a lawyer to obtain general advice about your matter.</p><p style="text-align: center;">You can contact the Helpline on 1300 654 314 to make an appointment.</p><p style="text-align: center;">2. Free telephone information and/or advice with a paralegal or lawyer. Please contact</p><p style="text-align: center;">the Helpline on 1300 654 314.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">2 Allsop Street Canberra City Phone (02) 6243 3411 legalaid@legalaidACT.org.au</p><p style="text-align: center;">GPO Box 512 Canberra ACT 2601 Fax (02) 6243 3435 www.legalaidACT.org.au ABN 40 848 011 291</p><p style="text-align: center;">You are entitled to have this decision reviewed by requesting that the Chief Executive</p><p style="text-align: center;">Officer convene a Review Committee which is bound to follow guidelines set by the</p><p style="text-align: center;">Commission and Commonwealth. If you want to do so, please send your request in writing</p><p style="text-align: center;">within 28 days.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Yours sincerely</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Client Services</p><p style="text-align: center;">Leg